==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wægn|wæġn]]'', from Germanic ''wagna-'', from Indo-European ''*wegh-''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[wagen]]'', German ''[[Wagen]]'', Swedish ''[[vagn]]''.  Compare ''[[wagon]]''.

